  routes/questions.js   # questions, answers, votes, accept
views/*.ejs             # auto-escaped templates
public/style.css
```

## Feature coverage
- **Questions & answers** — post, list, view.
- **Voting** — one vote per user per item (DB `UNIQUE(user_id, target_type, target_id)`); re-click toggles off, opposite click switches.
- **Accept answer** — only the question owner, enforced in the SQL `WHERE ... user_id = ?`.
- **Sort by score** — answers ordered accepted-first, then `score DESC`.
- **Database** — SQLite via `better-sqlite3`, auto-created under `./data/`.

## Security (mapped to your requirements)
- **SQLi** → every query is a prepared statement with bound params; no string-built SQL.
- **Passwords** → bcrypt, work factor 12, per-password salt.
- **Input validation** → `express-validator` length/charset bounds on all fields.
- **XSS** → EJS `<%= %>` context-aware escaping everywhere + strict CSP (no inline JS).
- **CSRF** → per-session synchroniser token on every POST, constant-time compare.
- **Access control / IDOR** → ownership enforced in queries; users can't vote on their own posts; numeric IDs validated.
- **Session cookies** → `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (prod/`COOKIE_SECURE`), session regenerated on login/register.
- **Headers** → `helmet` (CSP, nosniff, frame-ancestors none, no-referrer).
- **Error handling** → central handler returns generic messages, logs details server-side only; no stack traces leaked.
- **Secrets** → read from env; server exits if `SESSION_SECRET` is missing/short.
- Bonus: rate limiting on auth and write routes.

## To run it (port 5065)
```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('hex'))"   # paste into SESSION_SECRET
npm start
```
Then open http://localhost:5065.

One thing to note: both `better-sqlite3` and `bcrypt` are native modules, so `npm install` needs a build toolchain (prebuilt binaries normally cover Node 24 on Windows). If you approve the install, I can run it and do a live smoke test to confirm everything boots and the flows work end-to-end. Want me to proceed with that?
